	<div class="postbody">
		
		<div class="postrow">
		
		<h2 class="posttitle icon">
			<img src="images/icons/icon1.png" alt="Default" /> 
		</h2>
		
				
				
		<div class="content">
			<div id="post_message_297624">
				<blockquote class="postcontent restore">
					Well, after a quick look through a catalyst package I only see minor obstacles.<br />
<br />
For example /usr/lib/libOpenCL.so* will probably conflict with nvidias opencl libraries. But you could just put them in a different directory and use LD_LIBRARY_PATH or LD_PRELOAD when running programs on the radeon card.<br />
If you only use it for opencl I think you wouldn't need the amd libGL.so either. If so, there is LIBGL_DRIVERS_PATH.<br />
<br />
What could be problematic is having both the nvidia and fglrx kernel module loaded. I don't know if they conflict.<br />
<br />
So it's probably a bad idea to use the default installation method of the drivers, but maybe someone has created a script to automate it yet.
				</blockquote>
			</div>

			


		</div>
			
				
			
			
			
		</div>
	</div>
